When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

  Remote repositories would be helpful when working on more than one machine or when collaborating with others. 

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

  If you are working on something that is not yet ready to share, or isn't working right, you might want to hold it in local until it is ready,and then push it manually.
  

